article.headline: Duke surges to Junkanoo final
article.linkText: Duke holds Stephen F. Austin to 29 points
article.story:
FREEPORT, Bahamas (AP) -- Monique Currie scored 22 points to lead
Duke (No. 9 ESPN/USA Today; No. 10 AP) to an 84-29 victory over Stephen F. Austin in the
opening round of the Junkanoo Jam on Friday night.

Currie shot 7 for 13 and finished with 10 rebounds, three steals
and three assists for the Blue Devils (4-1), who face 16th-ranked
Kansas State in Saturday's championship game.

Kansas State reached the title game with a 105-61 win over
Illinois State.

Alison Bales had 13 points, 14 rebounds and five blocked shots,
and helped Duke to a 64-38 rebounding advantage. Change Black added
12 points and 10 rebounds for Duke, which led 45-15 at the break.

Jennifer Simpson had eight points and eight rebounds for the
Ladyjacks (0-2).
